d dialectical meditation on the history of utopian thinking as a quintessential history of modernity.As he unravels the dialectics at work in the utopian narrative, Wegner gives an ambitious synthetic discussion of theories of modernity, considering and evaluating the ideas of writers such as Ernst Bloch, Louis Marin, Gilles Deleuze, Walter Benjamin, Martin Heidegger, Henri Lefebvre, Paul de Man, Karl Mannheim, Mikhail Bakhtin, Jürgen Habermas, Slavoj Zizek, and Homi Bhabha.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAmerican fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aCommunities in literature. 0aCommunity in literature. 0aComparative literaturexAmerican and Russian. 0aComparative literaturexRussian and American. 0aModernism (Literature)zGreat Britain. 0aModernism (Literature)zRussia. 0aModernism (Literature)zUnited States. 0aNationalism in literature. 0aRussian fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aSpace and time in literature. 0aUtopias in literature. 0aUtopias. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh  a16th century.  a19th century.  a20th century.  acriticism.  acritique.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  aernst bloch.  agilles deleuze.  ahenri lefebvre.  ahomi bhabha.  ajurgen habermas.  akarl mannheim.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary history.  aliterary.  alouis marin.  amartin heidegger.  amikhail bakhtin.  amodernity.  anation state.  apaul de man.  aphilosophical.  aphilosophy.  apolitical.  apolitics.  aslavoj zizek.  asocial history.  asocial studies.  asocial theory.  athomas more.  autopian narrative.  autopian theory.  autopian.  autopianism.  awalter benjamin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022829040u